Kodhek became the first Kenyan to open a private law firm in 1957 at the height of Mau Mau resistance. The former Gem MP has lately been warming up to ODM and Raila. Roads and Infrastructure, Agriculture, Water, Health and Education are the top agenda of the current political term The event was cancelled after the judge arrived late. Interior CS Fred Matiang'i was among leaders who went to Lee Funeral Home to condole with the family. His family says he had difficulty breathing after his lungs collapsed.